OL,3,CGas firm to face criminal charge over
OL,4,Cexplosion in family home
OL,6,FThe children were unharmed and the
OL,7,Fparents had non-life-changing
OL,8,Finjuries, but their home was partially
OL,9,Fdestroyed and nearby properties were
OL,10,Fevacuated as a major incident was
OL,11,Fdeclared.
OL,13,FJersey's Fire and Rescue Service later
OL,14,Fstated that it is "reasonable to
OL,15,Fconclude an explosion occurred due to
OL,16,Fignition of a mixture of a flammable
OL,17,Fgas and air that accumulated within
OL,18,Fthe property".
